Some people think the government should ban smoking in public places. Others believe individuals should be free to choose. Discuss both views and give your opinion.

exposes non-smokers to second-hand smoke
health awareness
gradual decrease
violate individual freedom 
infringe on personal freedom
undermine civil liberties 

With health awareness growing,  the smoking rate has been gradully descresing lately. However, there are still some places are allowed to smoke such as resturants, park, and even on the street in China. Some argue that government should ban smoking in public places, while others disagree due to it could be undermine civil right. In this essay, I will examine both perspectives and illustrate my point of view.




你原句
However, there are still some places are allowed to smoke such as resturants, park, and even on the street in China.
✅ 改成：
However, smoking is still permitted in certain public places, such as restaurants, parks, and even on the streets in some countries, including China

你原句
Some argue that government should ban smoking in public places, while others disagree due to it could be undermine civil right.
❌ 这是最大扣分点
✅ 改成：
Some argue that governments should ban smoking in public areas, while others oppose such measures on the grounds that they may infringe on individual freedom.

你原句
In this essay, I will examine both perspectives and illustrate my point of view.
✅ 改成（更 Band 7+）：
This essay will examine both perspectives before presenting my own view


1.固定表达块背诵法
	高价值 IELTS 搭配块（直接背）
		smoking is permitted / restricted / banned
		pose a threat / risk
		infringe on freedom / rights
		play a role in
		lead to / result in health problems
2.错误清单固化法
	你现在就该开始一个清单，名字可以叫：
	❌「我写过但不自然的句型」
	例如：
	❌ places are allowed to smoke
	✅ smoking is allowed in places
	❌ due to + clause
	✅ due to + noun phrase

